NT|^B@2
South expects to lose two diamond tricks, one club, and one spade in addition to the trump suit. Even if South got a normal split, he might lose three trump tricks if the finesse loses. However, he doesn't have any choice. He just has to play trump and hope for the best. There is no reason not to. When you have a decision as to whether to draw trump or not, ask yourself “Is there any reason not to draw trump?” And, on most hands, there is a definite logical reason. But there is no advantage here.|
